{"type":"message","id":"6d588f69","parentId":"e893786a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:50:26.379Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"function.exec:36","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — Pairing codes exist because even bots believe in consent—and good security hygiene.\n\nUsage: openclaw agents [options] [command]\n\nManage isolated agents (workspaces + auth + routing)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add a new isolated agent\n  bind          Add routing bindings for an agent\n  bindings      List routing bindings\n  delete        Delete an agent and prune workspace/state\n  list          List configured agents\n  set-identity  Update an agent identity (name/theme/emoji/avatar)\n  unbind        Remove routing bindings for an agent\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agents"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3296,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — Pairing codes exist because even bots believe in consent—and good security hygiene.\n\nUsage: openclaw agents [options] [command]\n\nManage isolated agents (workspaces + auth + routing)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add a new isolated agent\n  bind          Add routing bindings for an agent\n  bindings      List routing bindings\n  delete        Delete an agent and prune workspace/state\n  list          List configured agents\n  set-identity  Update an agent identity (name/theme/emoji/avatar)\n  unbind        Remove routing bindings for an agent\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agents","cwd":"/home/lcc/.openclaw/workspace-manager"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772988626367}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a72374e","parentId":"6d588f69","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:50:29.621Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"看来 `openclaw agents run` 命令的语法不对。让我查看正确的使用方式："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"function.exec:37","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw --help 2>&1 | head -50"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772988626380}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b2db011","parentId":"3a72374e","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:50:32.768Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"function.exec:37","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — Built by lobsters, for humans. Don't question the hierarchy.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts setup\n                       wizard.\n  configure            Interactive setup wizard for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  memory *             Search and reindex memory files\n  message *            Send, read, and manage messages\n  models *             Discover, scan, and configure models"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3140,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — Built by lobsters, for humans. Don't question the hierarchy.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts setup\n                       wizard.\n  configure            Interactive setup wizard for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  memory *             Search and reindex memory files\n  message *            Send, read, and manage messages\n  models *             Discover, scan, and configure models","cwd":"/home/lcc/.openclaw/workspace-manager"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772988632763}}
{"type":"message","id":"e1aa496b","parentId":"6b2db011","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:50:34.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"function.exec:38","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772988632768}}
{"type":"message","id":"29d0e218","parentId":"e1aa496b","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:50:37.602Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"function.exec:38","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — I'm the reason your shell history looks like a hacker-movie montage.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3256,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — I'm the reason your shell history looks like a hacker-movie montage.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"/home/lcc/.openclaw/workspace-manager"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772988637591}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffa024c0","parentId":"29d0e218","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:50:40.987Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"让我直接使用 `curl` 来搜索一些 AI 新闻网站，或者尝试用其他方式："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"function.exec:39","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://www.bing.com/news/search?q=AI人工智能+最新\" -H \"User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0\" 2>/dev/null | grep -oP '(?<=<a[^>]*href=\"https://[^\"]*\"[^>]*>)[^<]+' | head -10 || echo \"无法获取Bing新闻\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772988637602}}
